# Cross-Browser Extension Compatibility

Always assume the browser extension runs in **both Firefox and Chrome**.

## Manifest

- Use both `background.scripts` (Firefox) and `background.service_worker` (Chrome) in `manifest.json`.
- `"world": "MAIN"` in content scripts is Chrome-only; Firefox ignores or errors on it. Use messaging between an isolated-world content script and a MAIN-world injected script when page-context access is needed in Firefox.

## APIs

- Use the `chrome.*` namespace (Firefox supports it via polyfill/compat in MV3).
- Avoid Chrome-only APIs without checking availability first (e.g. `chrome.offscreen`, `chrome.sidePanel`).
- `chrome.scripting.executeScript` works in both, but parameter shapes can differ — test both.

## Testing Reminder

When adding or changing extension features, call out any Firefox/Chrome behavioral differences in your response.
